main event: An unidentified object approached an aircraft during a training mission on 1 March 1950.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar traveling at a speed of approximately 600 mph.,The interaction lasted for about four minutes.,The object faded from view after the aircraft executed a 90-degree turn.,The report was filed by the North Atlantic Hq. Strategic Air Command.,The incident occurred 500 miles southeast of Newfoundland.
